using (var connection = new SqlConnection(connectionString))\n{\n    var command = new SqlCommand("dbo.proc_StatsDay", connection)\n    {\n        CommandType = CommandType.StoredProcedure\n    };\n\n    // Add parameters if there are any for the stored procedure.\n    command.Parameters.AddWithValue("@columns", "location1,location2,location3,");\n\n    using (SqlDataAdapter adapter = new SqlDataAdapter(command))\n    {\n        DataTable table = new DataTable();\n        adapter.Fill(table);\n        \n        foreach (DataRow row in table.Rows)\n        {\n            Console.WriteLine(row["OrderTime"].ToString());\n            // You can access other dynamically created columns by name.\n            if (row.Table.Columns.Contains("Location1"))\n                Console.WriteLine(row["Location1"].ToString());\n            if (row.Table.Columns.Contains("Location2"))\n                Console.WriteLine(row["Location2"].ToString());\n            if (row.Table.Columns.Contains("Location3"))\n                Console.WriteLine(row["Location3"].ToString());\n        }\n    }\n}